  "prompt": "How do you put on fake eyelashes without glue?",
  "response": "Here are some alternative methods to apply fake eyelashes without traditional glue:\n\n1. Magnetic eyelashes\n- These come with tiny magnets that attach to each other, sandwiching your natural lashes\n- Simply align the top and bottom magnetic strips near your lash line\n- No adhesive required\n\n2. Adhesive strips\n- Use pre-glued eyelash strips that have a sticky backing\n- Peel off the protective layer and apply directly to your lash line\n- These are easier to apply and remove than traditional glue\n\n3. Eyelash adhesive tape\n- Special double-sided tape designed specifically for false lashes\n- Cut to fit your lash band\n- Press onto your lash line and attach the lashes\n\n4. Magnetic eyeliner method\n- Apply a magnetic eyeliner\n- The magnetic lashes will stick to the liner\n- Requires purchasing special magnetic eyeliner and lashes\n\n5. Self-adhesive lashes\n- Some false lashes come with a built-in adhesive strip\n- Simply peel and stick onto your lash line\n- Often easier to apply than traditional glue\n\nEach method has pros and cons, so experiment to find what works best for you.",
